            <div id="dsq-comment-message-8593" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>The line<br />
int mid = (start + end)/2;<br />
should be changed to ceiling((start + end)/2) if we want the tree for [1, 2, 3, 4] as shown in the diagram. If we don&#8217;t have a ceiling function we can do like<br />
int sum = start + end;<br />
int floor = sum /2;<br />
int ceiling = floor + sum &#8211; floor * 2;</p>
<p>Thanks,<br />
Ashu</p>
